You live in this city.

239
00:11:59.885 --> 00:12:02.262
- I know. I know. It's so weird. I…
- Oh. Oh.

240
00:12:02.263 --> 00:12:04.514
- Oh my God.
- Man. I am so mixed up.

241
00:12:04.515 --> 00:12:06.015
Oh my God.

242
00:12:06.016 --> 00:12:07.350
I'm so sorry about that. Bye.

243
00:12:11.731 --> 00:12:13.440
It started after we played the McShays.

244
00:12:13.441 --> 00:12:14.607
Ow!

245
00:12:14.608 --> 00:12:16.818
Stop not telling me
when you hook up with Jay!

246
00:12:16.819 --> 00:12:17.861
We kept texting.

247
00:12:17.862 --> 00:12:20.864
and then when we made the finals.
it just became. like. a thing.

248
00:12:20.865 --> 00:12:23.241
Wow. So… so you're. like. dating?

249
00:12:23.242 --> 00:12:25.201
We're keeping it casual.
Living in the moment.

250
00:12:26.287 --> 00:12:29.372
What? Ali.
long-distance relationships can work.

251
00:12:29.373 --> 00:12:30.749
I'm not trying to be harsh.

252
00:12:30.750 --> 00:12:32.500
I know you're just living in the moment.

253
00:12:32.501 --> 00:12:35.087
but this moment is also
your chance to win a title.

254
00:12:36.505 --> 00:12:38.298
It's not the best timing. I'll admit it.

255
00:12:38.299 --> 00:12:40.717
Also. kinda risky
sleeping with the enemy during wartime.

256
00:12:40.718 --> 00:12:44.262
I'm not giving him our game plan
when we're. you know…

257
00:12:44.263 --> 00:12:46.306
Not that it'd matter.
Jay doesn't need help.

258
00:12:46.307 --> 00:12:48.308
Boston's dominated
every team in the playoffs.

259
00:12:48.309 --> 00:12:49.851
Not everyone. Not Chicago.

260
00:12:49.852 --> 00:12:50.686
True.

261
00:12:54.690 --> 00:12:56.734
- What?
- Get Ness in here right now.

262
00:13:01.322 --> 00:13:04.157
Boston won every series
by an average of nine points a game.

263
00:13:04.158 --> 00:13:05.158
except Chicago.

264
00:13:05.159 --> 00:13:07.160
That series.
they only won by three a game.

265
00:13:07.161 --> 00:13:08.871
And two of those games went to overtime.

266
00:13:09.455 --> 00:13:11.248
So what did Chicago do differently?

267
00:13:11.999 --> 00:13:15.460
They went small.
Four guards and a power forward.

268
00:13:15.461 --> 00:13:18.047
Zone. nonstop press.
Totally changed up their game.

269
00:13:18.964 --> 00:13:20.548
We're gonna go Chicago-style.

270
00:13:20.549 --> 00:13:23.134
Attack from the wings.
put Turner and Kuman in foul trouble.

271
00:13:23.135 --> 00:13:24.804
take away their biggest advantage.

272
00:13:25.304 --> 00:13:26.471
Ness. what do we think?

273
00:13:26.472 --> 00:13:27.932
Chicago-style.

274
00:13:29.350 --> 00:13:30.476
I like it.

275
00:13:31.477 --> 00:13:35.396
It's also making me really want
some pizza. I'll get into it with Coach.

276
00:13:37.525 --> 00:13:39.276
I wish you'd thought of this
three games ago.

277
00:13:48.035 --> 00:13:48.952
Hey.

278
00:13:48.953 --> 00:13:50.204
Can we talk?

279
00:13:51.205 --> 00:13:55.792
I'm wondering if this is getting
a little… too complicated.

280
00:13:55.793 --> 00:13:58.294
and maybe we should push pause for a bit.

281
00:13:58.295 --> 00:14:00.672
- Is this because Ali saw me naked?
- No. no. no.

282
00:14:00.673 --> 00:14:04.051
I just…
I'm having a hard time focusing. I think.

283
00:14:05.511 --> 00:14:06.887
Focusing or losing?

284
00:14:07.388 --> 00:14:10.431
Come on. Don't tell me you wouldn't feel
similarly if you were down 0-3.

285
00:14:10.432 --> 00:14:14.227
Yeah. but I thought we talked about
keeping this and basketball separate.

286
00:14:14.228 --> 00:14:18.356
Yeah. well. we also didn't have pants on
when we made that decision. so…

287
00:14:18.357 --> 00:14:21.569
Can't we just figure this out
when the finals are over?

288
00:14:22.736 --> 00:14:23.571
Sure.

289
00:14:24.488 --> 00:14:25.322
Yeah.

290
00:14:26.740 --> 00:14:28.200
I can wait one more game.

291
00:14:30.953 --> 00:14:32.246
Are you talking shit?

292
00:14:32.746 --> 00:14:34.790
I mean. we're rivals again. so…

293
00:14:36.917 --> 00:14:37.751
Okay.

294
00:14:38.335 --> 00:14:39.419
Okay.

295
00:14:39.420 --> 00:14:41.338
Good luck.

296
00:14:52.057 --> 00:14:55.310
{\an8}<i>And a shorthanded LA team
staves off elimination.</i>

297
00:14:55.311 --> 00:14:58.229
<i>but Boston's still up three games to one.</i>

298
00:14:58.230 --> 00:15:01.065
I mean. come on.
Chicago-style totally worked.

299
00:15:01.066 --> 00:15:02.942
Ooh. Jay was flustered the whole game.

300
00:15:02.943 --> 00:15:05.528
Did you see when he was choking
on Gatorade and started coughing?

301
00:15:05.529 --> 00:15:08.698
It was nice to see
his hot face sweaty and bloated.

302
00:15:08.699 --> 00:15:09.991
just like the rest of us.

303
00:15:09.992 --> 00:15:11.576
Any update on Marcus?

304
00:15:11.577 --> 00:15:13.536
No. Ray and Roy both have
their phones off.

305
00:15:13.537 --> 00:15:17.123
I know he's pissed. but he should be
sitting on the bench supporting the guys.

306
00:15:17.124 --> 00:15:19.042
It's fine. all right?
We're gonna find him.

307
00:15:19.043 --> 00:15:20.084
Cheer up.

308
00:15:20.085 --> 00:15:21.586
- You okay?
- Oh. sorry. Too hard?

309
00:15:22.880 --> 00:15:24.005
Is that your tooth?

310
00:15:24.006 --> 00:15:26.841
It's from all the gum you've been chewing.
Bitch. you just lost a tooth.

311
00:15:26.842 --> 00:15:29.260
We're gonna take you to the dentist
as soon as we get to LA.

312
00:15:29.261 --> 00:15:31.220
Jackie. go around! Drive! Jesus!

313
00:15:31.221 --> 00:15:34.475
We should look into separate flights home.
That could be contagious.

314
00:15:36.644 --> 00:15:38.812
Okay. Gene. just stay there for the month.

315
00:15:39.897 --> 00:15:42.565
Oh my God. I wasn't serious.

316
00:15:43.984 --> 00:15:45.945
Hey. everything okay?

317
00:15:46.445 --> 00:15:50.615
No. my husband wants to move
to Austin for his "stand-up" career.

318
00:15:50.616 --> 00:15:53.326
He thinks he's got a shot
at being Theo Von's assistant.

319
00:15:53.327 --> 00:15:54.327
Oh.

320
00:15:54.328 --> 00:15:55.496
Anyway. what's up?

321
00:15:56.538 --> 00:15:58.706
I think you should come
on the scouting trip.

322
00:15:58.707 --> 00:16:00.708
- What?
- You know the game.

323
00:16:00.709 --> 00:16:04.045
You're good at pointing out people's flaws
that make 'em human and weak.

324
00:16:04.046 --> 00:16:06.172
- I… I don't know. Ness.
- I could use the help.

325
00:16:06.173 --> 00:16:08.049
I mean. these kids see me
as the fun uncle.

326
00:16:08.968 --> 00:16:10.969
It'd be good to know
they have a bitchy tiger mom.

327
00:16:10.970 --> 00:16:12.553
You could've just said tiger mom.

328
00:16:12.554 --> 00:16:14.055
Tiger mom.

329
00:16:14.056 --> 00:16:15.099
You know what?

330
00:16:17.351 --> 00:16:18.352
I'm in.

331
00:16:18.852 --> 00:16:19.979
All right.

332
00:16:20.479 --> 00:16:23.189
Just so you know. last time
I went transatlantic. I took an Ambien.

333
00:16:23.190 --> 00:16:25.942
and I just kinda wandered the aisles.
but I sorted that out.

334
00:16:25.943 --> 00:16:26.985
Monica!

335
00:16:30.864 --> 00:16:31.699
Oh.

336
00:16:32.241 --> 00:16:35.034
Isla. you must start flossing.

337
00:16:35.035 --> 00:16:37.495
I do.

338
00:16:37.496 --> 00:16:40.748
I just removed
an entire Cobb salad out of your mouth.

339
00:16:40.749 --> 00:16:41.958
Oh. Mr. McShay!

340
00:16:41.959 --> 00:16:44.752
- Hi.
- It's so good to see your gums. as usual.

341
00:16:44.753 --> 00:16:47.630
And I don't know how.
but your teeth are getting straighter.

342
00:16:47.631 --> 00:16:48.631
Good genes. I guess.

343
00:16:51.593 --> 00:16:52.510
Hey.

344
00:16:52.511 --> 00:16:54.679
What are you doing here?
Getting new teeth for your hockey players?

345
00:16:54.680 --> 00:16:56.723
I've been coming to Dr. Weaver for years.

346
00:16:56.724 --> 00:16:57.682
Me too.

347
00:16:57.683 --> 00:17:01.269
He did my braces
when I was a kid and an adult.

348
00:17:01.270 --> 00:17:02.562
I mean. it's not a great flex.

349
00:17:03.605 --> 00:17:04.440
No.

350
00:17:05.024 --> 00:17:08.109
No. I'm a little off.
I haven't had solid foods all day.

351
00:17:08.110 --> 00:17:12.405
Well. lucky for you. this building has one
of the best restaurants in Los Angeles.

352
00:17:12.406 --> 00:17:13.406
Mmm.

353
00:17:13.407 --> 00:17:14.490
- Feeling better?
- Mm-hmm.

354
00:17:14.491 --> 00:17:17.368
- Blood sugar back to normal?
- Didn't this used to be a cigar lounge?

355
00:17:17.369 --> 00:17:20.663
And then a cupcake store
and a fedora shop.

356
00:17:20.664 --> 00:17:21.873
Mmm.

357
00:17:21.874 --> 00:17:24.042
So you're riding high
after that W last night?

358
00:17:24.043 --> 00:17:26.044
Yeah. Oh.

359
00:17:26.045 --> 00:17:26.961
We needed that.

360
00:17:26.962 --> 00:17:29.714
It was a good call changing up
the game plan. They weren't ready.

361
00:17:29.715 --> 00:17:30.715
You watched.

362
00:17:30.716 --> 00:17:33.718
Are you kidding? I'm from LA.
I love everything about this city.

363
00:17:33.719 --> 00:17:36.055
I mean. except the 405.

364
00:17:36.555 --> 00:17:37.472
The worst.

365
00:17:37.473 --> 00:17:39.932
- Oh. what about the 110? Horrible.
- Horrible.

366
00:17:39.933 --> 00:17:42.061
I love exiting from the left side
like an idiot.

367
00:17:43.687 --> 00:17:46.898
You see? I knew we'd have a good time
if we went out on a date.

368
00:17:46.899 --> 00:17:48.691
- This is not a date.
- It's not a date?

369
00:17:48.692 --> 00:17:51.320
No. it's two people talking
in a medical plaza.

370
00:17:51.904 --> 00:17:52.820
All right.

371
00:17:52.821 --> 00:17:55.907
- Well. let's do dinner next time.
- Not so fast.

372
00:17:55.908 --> 00:17:58.868
Maybe we'll run into each other
at the podiatrist.

373
00:18:01.330 --> 00:18:03.748
<i>Dyson for three. Good again!</i>

374
00:18:03.749 --> 00:18:06.417
{\an8}<i>And the Waves have come from behind
to win game five.</i>

375
00:18:06.418 --> 00:18:09.295
{\an8}<i>Game six has been all Waves.</i>

376
00:18:09.296 --> 00:18:10.755
<i>Travis to Tommy.</i>

377
00:18:10.756 --> 00:18:14.717
{\an8}<i>And the Waves win big in Boston
to force game seven.</i>

378
00:18:14.718 --> 00:18:16.469
<i>Insane win. John.</i>

379
00:18:16.470 --> 00:18:19.555
<i>Can Isla Gordon bring home
her first title as Team Pres?</i>

380
00:18:19.556 --> 00:18:20.974
<i>We'll find out tonight.</i>

381
00:18:22.684 --> 00:18:23.936
Jackie!

382
00:18:25.354 --> 00:18:27.605
Hey. any word if Marcus showed up yet?

383
00:18:27.606 --> 00:18:29.565
- Nothing.
- Oh. shit.

384
00:18:29.566 --> 00:18:31.818
I took away all your gum.
Dr. Weaver's orders.

385
00:18:31.819 --> 00:18:34.445
If you want something to chew on.
I have soft cheeses and oatmeal

386
00:18:34.446 --> 00:18:35.363
in the break room.

387
00:18:37.157 --> 00:18:38.117
Thanks.

388
00:18:40.077 --> 00:18:41.870
Jackie. sit down for a second.

389
00:18:45.124 --> 00:18:48.709
Look. Cam was wrong about a lot.
but he wasn't about one thing.

390
00:18:48.710 --> 00:18:50.086
That taxation is theft?

391
00:18:50.087 --> 00:18:51.003
No.

392
00:18:51.004 --> 00:18:53.006
You deserve more opportunity here.

393
00:18:53.715 --> 00:18:56.300
How'd you like to go with Ness
on the scouting trip to Europe?

394
00:18:56.301 --> 00:18:58.261
Are you serious?

395
00:18:58.262 --> 00:19:00.972
- Yes.
- I've been dying to visit Europe.

396
00:19:00.973 --> 00:19:03.015
Ooh. it's my favorite part
of It's a Small World.

397
00:19:03.016 --> 00:19:04.101
Great.

398
00:19:06.145 --> 00:19:07.771
But I think I have to pass.

399
00:19:09.189 --> 00:19:10.898
Really? Why?

400
00:19:10.899 --> 00:19:12.776
I've been meaning
to talk to you about this.

401
00:19:13.360 --> 00:19:15.528
You know Sofia's doing
her internship in DC.

402
00:19:15.529 --> 00:19:19.073
and I was kinda hoping
that I could take some time off

403
00:19:19.074 --> 00:19:20.449
to visit her for the summer.

404
00:19:20.450 --> 00:19:22.326
Oh. that's nice.

405
00:19:22.327 --> 00:19:23.328
Um…

406
00:19:24.037 --> 00:19:25.997
But what are you going to do
while you're there?

407
00:19:25.998 --> 00:19:30.252
Um. help her get ready
for work in the mornings. and then.

408
00:19:31.378 --> 00:19:33.172
I don't know. wait until she gets home.

409
00:19:33.755 --> 00:19:34.631
Jackie…

410
00:19:36.508 --> 00:19:38.342
I have this friend.

411
00:19:38.343 --> 00:19:44.265
and… she got offered
a dream job in Paris. and turned it down

412
00:19:44.266 --> 00:19:48.812
because she wanted
to spend the summer with her boyfriend.

413
00:19:49.479 --> 00:19:52.691
And then. a month later. they broke up.

414
00:19:53.192 --> 00:19:57.820
And she will always be known
as the girl who didn't go to Paris.

415
00:19:57.821 --> 00:19:58.822
Wow.

416
00:19:59.406 --> 00:20:01.866
That sounds just like LC from <i>The Hills</i>.

417
00:20:01.867 --> 00:20:05.328
It is LC from <i>The Hills</i>.
She's my friend. I love her.

418
00:20:05.329 --> 00:20:08.957
But… do you want to be like LC?

419
00:20:14.171 --> 00:20:17.048
{\an8}<i>Welcome to game seven
of the ABL Finals.</i>

420
00:20:17.049 --> 00:20:20.719
{\an8}<i>LA versus Boston. Winner take all.</i>

421
00:20:21.220 --> 00:20:22.971
- You ready? Nervous?
- Hmm.

422
00:20:23.805 --> 00:20:25.598
A little bit of both.

423
00:20:27.351 --> 00:20:30.144
All right. let's go have
the best or worst night of my life.

424
00:20:45.619 --> 00:20:46.786
- It'll be fun.
- Good luck.

425
00:20:46.787 --> 00:20:47.703
You too.

426
00:20:49.665 --> 00:20:52.041
<i>Sign up for
an official Waves credit card</i>

427
00:20:52.042 --> 00:20:53.709
<i>and receive a free miniature…</i>

428
00:20:56.213 --> 00:20:58.089
I can't believe Marcus is still MIA.

429
00:20:58.090 --> 00:21:01.217
God. he can hate me all he wants.
but it's insane he's not here.

430
00:21:01.218 --> 00:21:03.636
<i>Make some noise!</i>

431
00:21:03.637 --> 00:21:05.471
<i>All right. we're about ready to go.</i>

432
00:21:05.472 --> 00:21:07.473
<i>Game seven. You ready. Edgar?</i>

433
00:21:07.474 --> 00:21:10.059
<i>I'm ready
to run through a brick wall. John.</i>

434
00:21:10.060 --> 00:21:11.894
<i>Maybe after the game.</i>

435
00:21:11.895 --> 00:21:13.062
<i>And we're off.</i>

436
00:21:13.063 --> 00:21:16.984
<i>Boston controls it.
and Howard leaps for the quick dunk.</i>

437
00:21:17.567 --> 00:21:19.277
<i>Waves' ball.</i>

438
00:21:19.278 --> 00:21:21.321
<i>White calls out the play.</i>

439
00:21:22.781 --> 00:21:24.824
<i>Dyson off the curl.</i>

440
00:21:24.825 --> 00:21:25.909
<i>Not close.</i>

441
00:21:26.410 --> 00:21:30.121
<i>He's off early.
and Howard with another easy one.</i>

442
00:21:30.122 --> 00:21:31.455
Put a body on him.

443
00:21:31.456 --> 00:21:32.498
<i>He's killing us.</i>

444
00:21:32.499 --> 00:21:35.501
<i>And a much bigger Boston team
is coming out hot.</i>

445
00:21:35.502 --> 00:21:36.670
Come on. Come on.

446
00:21:37.713 --> 00:21:40.173
- <i>Tommy is stripped.</i>
- Get back. Get back.

447
00:21:41.425 --> 00:21:42.883
<i>LA's down 20.</i>

448
00:21:42.884 --> 00:21:45.928
<i>Jay Brown and Boston have figured
out how to handle LA's new scheme</i>

449
00:21:45.929 --> 00:21:48.097
<i>with a counterattack of their own.</i>

450
00:21:53.020 --> 00:21:55.689
- Mmm. Sorry.
- Thank you. Thank you.

451
00:21:56.189 --> 00:21:57.273
Is that a mai tai?

452
00:21:57.274 --> 00:21:59.108
- This is an AMF.
- AMF?

453
00:21:59.109 --> 00:22:00.109
Goodbye. motherfucker.

454
00:22:00.110 --> 00:22:02.028
- Jackie.
- That's what the drink's called.

455
00:22:02.029 --> 00:22:04.155
Yes. brother.

456
00:22:04.156 --> 00:22:07.033
I'm thinking
we should go to Dubrovnik for a day.

457
00:22:07.034 --> 00:22:09.994
Because they got this kid
that can drain threes from half court.

458
00:22:09.995 --> 00:22:12.163
Plus. shrimp capital of Eastern Europe.

459
00:22:12.164 --> 00:22:13.998
Look. if it's got a beach. I'm in.

460
00:22:13.999 --> 00:22:16.417
What. are you guys planning
a work trip or your honeymoon?

461
00:22:16.418 --> 00:22:17.501
What?

462
00:22:17.502 --> 00:22:19.003
What are you talking about. Sandy?

463
00:22:19.004 --> 00:22:22.673
I get the Cam situation is making
you anxious. but you're a sloppy drunk.

464
00:22:22.674 --> 00:22:25.301
You need a cup of coffee.
Gail. can we get a coffee?

465
00:22:25.302 --> 00:22:26.344
Yeah. we're done.

466
00:22:26.345 --> 00:22:28.512
Coffee and an AMF. Gail.

467
00:22:28.513 --> 00:22:29.555
Shh. shh. shh. shh.

468
00:22:29.556 --> 00:22:31.349
<i>We're almost ready
for the second half.</i>

469
00:22:31.350 --> 00:22:34.685
<i>but the Waves without Marcus Winfield
are down big.</i>

470
00:22:34.686 --> 00:22:35.812
Jay is pretty focused.

471
00:22:37.939 --> 00:22:38.982
All right. guys.

472
00:22:39.483 --> 00:22:42.193
I know it may seem impossible right now.

473
00:22:42.194 --> 00:22:45.363
and it might be impossible.
but that doesn't mean it's not possible.

474
00:22:45.364 --> 00:22:47.198
Coach. that's literally what it means.

475
00:22:51.536 --> 00:22:54.663
<i>Now entering
the arena. Marcus Winfield!</i>

476
00:22:54.664 --> 00:22:56.999
- Where the hell you been?
- China. baby.

477
00:22:57.000 --> 00:22:58.751
Just got back an hour ago.

478
00:22:58.752 --> 00:23:00.002
Whoa. whoa. What?

479
00:23:00.003 --> 00:23:01.379
There's a lab in Chengdu.

480
00:23:01.380 --> 00:23:03.881
They have experimental therapy
that isn't available anywhere else.

481
00:23:03.882 --> 00:23:05.716
- Can you play?
- I'm playing.

482
00:23:05.717 --> 00:23:07.511
- Yeah!
- All right. All right.

483
00:23:08.011 --> 00:23:09.763
Hey. listen. guys. One more thing.

484
00:23:10.472 --> 00:23:15.351
I want to tell you all
about the night that I met my late wife.

485
00:23:15.352 --> 00:23:17.311
It was October 1990.

486
00:23:17.312 --> 00:23:22.901
And I know that because it was
the original Aunt Viv from <i>Fresh Prince</i>.

487
00:23:23.443 --> 00:23:25.945
It might have been '91.
and I was watching <i>Roseanne</i>.

488
00:23:25.946 --> 00:23:28.448
- The point is...
- All right. Coach. Do you mind?

489
00:23:29.324 --> 00:23:31.117
Let me help you out.

490
00:23:31.118 --> 00:23:32.993
Yeah. thank you.

491
00:23:32.994 --> 00:23:36.247
Look. we all know
you miss your dead wife. all right?

492
00:23:36.248 --> 00:23:38.959
But if she's watching right now.
she wants one thing.

493
00:23:39.459 --> 00:23:41.627
To win this fucking game!

494
00:23:43.255 --> 00:23:44.588
Waves on three!

495
00:23:44.589 --> 00:23:46.591
- One. two. three. Waves!
- Waves!

496
00:23:47.092 --> 00:23:48.217
It was <i>Golden Girls</i>.

497
00:23:48.218 --> 00:23:49.343
<i>I don't believe it.</i>

498
00:23:49.344 --> 00:23:53.056
<i>Look at this. Marcus Winfield is starting
the second half.</i>

499
00:23:53.849 --> 00:23:55.182
Where have you been?

500
00:23:55.183 --> 00:23:58.061
You told me to get better.
so… I got better.

501
00:24:01.231 --> 00:24:04.191
<i>And we're underway
in the second half.</i>

502
00:24:04.192 --> 00:24:07.988
<i>Marcus Winfield is back.
and he's picking up full court.</i>

503
00:24:08.780 --> 00:24:11.991
<i>He pokes it away from Turner.
Winfield on a breakaway.</i>

504
00:24:11.992 --> 00:24:14.326
<i>Bucket and a foul!</i>

505
00:24:14.327 --> 00:24:16.245
- And one!
- What? Who?

506
00:24:16.246 --> 00:24:17.872
That's Turner's fourth. Very good!

507
00:24:17.873 --> 00:24:19.582
<i>Waves on the attack again.</i>

508
00:24:19.583 --> 00:24:20.749
<i>Tommy White penetrates.</i>

509
00:24:20.750 --> 00:24:22.543
Don't give him that! Don't give him that!

510
00:24:22.544 --> 00:24:23.670
<i>To Marcus.</i>

511
00:24:24.713 --> 00:24:26.131
<i>It's good!</i>

512
00:24:26.882 --> 00:24:28.216
Pressure. guys. Pressure!

513
00:24:29.342 --> 00:24:30.426
Defense!

514
00:24:30.427 --> 00:24:33.179
<i>LA continues
the defensive pressure. Turner has it.</i>

515
00:24:33.180 --> 00:24:34.473
<i>He… misses.</i>

516
00:24:35.390 --> 00:24:36.682
<i>Up ahead to Gibbs.</i>

517
00:24:36.683 --> 00:24:39.060
<i>He finds Tommy for three.</i>

518
00:24:39.811 --> 00:24:41.354
<i>It's good!</i>

519
00:24:42.272 --> 00:24:44.274
We need a stop. We need a stop.

520
00:24:45.025 --> 00:24:47.693
<i>LA's defense has
turned it up a notch.</i>

521
00:24:47.694 --> 00:24:48.778
<i>Another steal.</i>

522
00:24:49.362 --> 00:24:51.780
<i>Atkins leaves it for Edwards.</i>

523
00:24:51.781 --> 00:24:54.533
<i>Slam dunk!</i>

524
00:24:54.534 --> 00:24:56.453
He's panicking. Jay's panicking.

525
00:24:58.914 --> 00:25:00.623
<i>Less than a minute to go. John.</i>

526
00:25:00.624 --> 00:25:03.459
<i>The Waves gotta get something
on this possession.</i>

527
00:25:04.878 --> 00:25:05.961
<i>Foul!</i>

528
00:25:05.962 --> 00:25:09.633
<i>Adrian Turner.
Boston's leading scorer. has fouled out.</i>

529
00:25:10.342 --> 00:25:12.718
<i>And LA has fought back.
Thirty seconds left.</i>

530
00:25:12.719 --> 00:25:14.595
<i>And now trails by four.</i>

531
00:25:14.596 --> 00:25:15.680
Let's go!

532
00:25:17.349 --> 00:25:18.265
Don't let up.

533
00:25:18.266 --> 00:25:19.725
<i>LA applying the pressure.</i>

534
00:25:19.726 --> 00:25:21.769
<i>Boston needs to get a shot off.</i>

535
00:25:21.770 --> 00:25:23.729
<i>- No good!</i>
- Get back! Get back!

536
00:25:23.730 --> 00:25:26.565
<i>LA needs a quick one here.
Ball goes to Victor in the corner.</i>

537
00:25:26.566 --> 00:25:28.025
<i>He swings it to Dyson.</i>

538
00:25:28.026 --> 00:25:30.069
<i>Gibbs for three!</i>

539
00:25:30.070 --> 00:25:31.862
<i>It's good!</i>

540
00:25:31.863 --> 00:25:33.322
<i>Waves down by one.</i>

541
00:25:33.323 --> 00:25:36.283
<i>Boston ball. Ten seconds left.</i>

542
00:25:36.284 --> 00:25:37.368
<i>LA's gotta foul!</i>

543
00:25:37.369 --> 00:25:40.829
- <i>Here's the game. Stolen by Marcus!</i>
- Time-out!

544
00:25:40.830 --> 00:25:42.207
<i>Time-out. Waves!</i>

545
00:25:42.707 --> 00:25:45.167
<i>He's playing like a man possessed.</i>

546
00:25:45.168 --> 00:25:47.461
- Whoa!
- Whoo!

547
00:25:47.462 --> 00:25:49.296
- Yes!
- Oh my God.

548
00:25:49.297 --> 00:25:52.091
I'm gonna throw up.
Ali. did you bring a vomit bag?

549
00:25:52.092 --> 00:25:53.384
Yes. but Ness already used it.

550
00:25:53.385 --> 00:25:56.011
Are you guys nervous.
or do you have norovirus?

551
00:25:56.012 --> 00:25:57.764
- Jesus.
- 'Cause of all the stress.

552
00:25:58.265 --> 00:25:59.682
<i>What a game.</i>

553
00:25:59.683 --> 00:26:02.226
<i>It all comes down to this.</i>

554
00:26:02.227 --> 00:26:03.978
<i>Game on the line.</i>

555
00:26:03.979 --> 00:26:05.229
<i>Title on the line.</i>

556
00:26:05.230 --> 00:26:07.147
<i>Waves have the ball.</i>

557
00:26:07.148 --> 00:26:08.399
<i>They bring it in to Tommy</i>

558
00:26:08.400 --> 00:26:10.943
<i>who gets it to Winfield
at the top of the key.</i>

559
00:26:10.944 --> 00:26:15.323
<i>Boston can't double Marcus
because LA's shooters have been red-hot.</i>

560
00:26:15.865 --> 00:26:19.035
<i>He drives. pulls it back…</i>

561
00:26:21.371 --> 00:26:22.497
<i>elevates.</i>

562
00:26:23.498 --> 00:26:24.874
<i>For the win…</i>

563
00:26:28.003 --> 00:26:30.254
You need to trade for
a shooting guard who can hit a three.

564
00:26:30.255 --> 00:26:31.797
You're gonna come work for us.

565
00:26:33.216 --> 00:26:35.718
I'm making you the president of the Waves.

566
00:26:35.719 --> 00:26:37.511
Done. Sending you a deal memo.

567
00:26:39.723 --> 00:26:43.100
There will always be
another playoffs that you choose over me.

568
00:26:52.736 --> 00:26:55.279
<i>It's good! It's good! It's good!</i>

569
00:26:55.280 --> 00:26:56.489
<i>Waves win!</i>

570
00:26:57.073 --> 00:26:58.908
<i>Marcus Winfield is the hero!</i>

571
00:26:59.451 --> 00:27:02.870
<i>The Waves are the world champions!</i>

572
00:27:29.439 --> 00:27:32.066
- Norm! You did it!
- All right. Hey.

573
00:27:32.984 --> 00:27:33.818
Yeah.

574
00:27:34.402 --> 00:27:38.906
Thank you. Thank you so much
for just believing in me. you know?

575
00:27:38.907 --> 00:27:40.783
I mean. when Andrea passed.

576
00:27:40.784 --> 00:27:45.204
I thought I would just be that old guy
who goes to the racetrack every day

577
00:27:45.205 --> 00:27:49.458
until the janitor comes
and sees me dead in the toilet stall.

578
00:27:49.459 --> 00:27:52.127
But you gave me
the dignity that I so badly needed.

579
00:27:52.128 --> 00:27:54.755
Norm. Norm. I… I love you. I love you.

580
00:27:54.756 --> 00:27:56.924
It's too… too heavy a conversation
for this time.

581
00:27:56.925 --> 00:27:58.175
- Okay.
- Congrats. Norm.

582
00:27:58.176 --> 00:27:59.093
You too.

583
00:28:00.720 --> 00:28:02.221
All right.

584
00:28:02.222 --> 00:28:03.139
- Hmm.
- We're good.

585
00:28:04.974 --> 00:28:09.019
- Yeah. I mean. I guess the best part...
- Champagne! That's the best part!

586
00:28:09.020 --> 00:28:10.730
Jackie. come here!

587
00:28:11.231 --> 00:28:13.023
Congrats. sis.

588
00:28:13.024 --> 00:28:15.526
So I told Sofia
I'm going to Europe this summer.

589
00:28:15.527 --> 00:28:17.403
Oh. that's amazing!

590
00:28:17.404 --> 00:28:18.697
How'd she take it?

591
00:28:19.197 --> 00:28:20.989
- Not well.
- Oh.

592
00:28:20.990 --> 00:28:23.535
But I didn't wanna be
the girl who didn't go to Paris.

593
00:28:24.035 --> 00:28:26.120
Oh. Ooh.

594
00:28:26.121 --> 00:28:27.414
Oh yeah!

595
00:28:29.249 --> 00:28:32.126
Brielle. will you make me
the luckiest man in the world?

596
00:28:32.127 --> 00:28:34.002
Will you have a threesome with me tonight?

597
00:28:34.003 --> 00:28:36.130
With that thot sitting courtside?

598
00:28:36.131 --> 00:28:38.341
- Yeah.
- Baby. I thought you'd never ask!

599
00:28:41.052 --> 00:28:42.679
Oh. Marcus.

600
00:28:44.305 --> 00:28:45.931
- We did it.
- Yeah.

601
00:28:45.932 --> 00:28:48.142
- Oh.
- Good news is it's not my knee.

602
00:28:48.143 --> 00:28:51.437
Oh good. That is very. very good news.

603
00:28:51.438 --> 00:28:52.981
It's my Achilles.

604
00:28:55.900 --> 00:28:56.776
What?

605
00:28:57.902 --> 00:29:00.113
- We gotta get you to Dr. Haber right...
- Later.

606
00:29:01.322 --> 00:29:04.575
I don't wanna spend my last moments
as a player inside a training room.

607
00:29:11.624 --> 00:29:12.959
Smile. We won.

608
00:29:16.379 --> 00:29:17.964
Oh. thank you. Marcus.

609
00:29:19.674 --> 00:29:20.675
Thank you.

610
00:29:22.552 --> 00:29:23.595
Now help me up.

611
00:29:24.262 --> 00:29:25.179
Please.

612
00:30:19.692 --> 00:30:20.859
Oh.

613
00:30:20.860 --> 00:30:22.319
God. he's so sweaty.

614
00:30:22.320 --> 00:30:26.031
If I would've known I'd be this hungover.
I maybe would've wanted to lose.

615
00:30:26.032 --> 00:30:29.618
No offense. but your voice sounds like
someone is drilling a hole in my brain.

616
00:30:31.663 --> 00:30:33.121
Oh God.

617
00:30:34.582 --> 00:30:35.874
Oh. I feel horrible.

618
00:30:37.627 --> 00:30:38.628
What?

619
00:30:39.128 --> 00:30:41.046
- Oh no.
- What is that?

620
00:30:41.047 --> 00:30:42.631
You passed out grilling steaks.

621
00:30:42.632 --> 00:30:44.466
- Oh!
- You need to go to the hospital.

622
00:30:44.467 --> 00:30:45.844
Turn the TV on right now.

623
00:30:46.344 --> 00:30:47.261
Jackie.

624
00:30:47.262 --> 00:30:49.012
Oh. what the f…

625
00:30:49.013 --> 00:30:52.558
<i>The LA Industry basketball franchise
was an integral part of this city.</i>

626
00:30:52.559 --> 00:30:54.393
- What is this.
<i>- Until it moved.</i>

627
00:30:54.394 --> 00:30:57.604
<i>But today. the Industry has returned.</i>

628
00:30:57.605 --> 00:31:02.359
<i>And we're gonna be the best
basketball team in Los Angeles!</i>

629
00:31:02.360 --> 00:31:03.610
Holy shit.

630
00:31:03.611 --> 00:31:04.611
What is happening?

631
00:31:04.612 --> 00:31:07.990
{\an8}<i>I am so honored
to partner with Al Fleischman</i>

632
00:31:07.991 --> 00:31:09.825
<i>to purchase the Industry.</i>

633
00:31:09.826 --> 00:31:14.329
<i>Uh. I've only known Al a short time.
but he's already become like family to me.</i>

634
00:31:14.330 --> 00:31:15.664
Oh my God.

635
00:31:15.665 --> 00:31:18.250
{\an8}<i>Now. if you're gonna have
a top-level basketball team.</i>

636
00:31:18.251 --> 00:31:20.627
{\an8}<i>you are gonna need a top-level coach.</i>

637
00:31:20.628 --> 00:31:23.672
{\an8}<i>so we pulled out all the stops
when we were hiring this guy.</i>

638
00:31:23.673 --> 00:31:26.466
{\an8}<i>Um. I am so honored to introduce</i>

639
00:31:26.467 --> 00:31:30.095
{\an8}<i>our new head coach
for the LA Industry and part owner.</i>

640
00:31:30.096 --> 00:31:31.013
{\an8}<i>Jay Brown.</i>

641
00:31:32.265 --> 00:31:33.223
{\an8}<i>Come here.</i>

642
00:31:34.934 --> 00:31:37.561
<i>Thanks. guys.
Come on. take a picture.</i>

643
00:31:39.689 --> 00:31:41.440
Motherfucker!
